I am not sure which component this belongs to, can you please assign it to the 
right component.

When starting WSAD 5.1.1 and choosing the workspace we have been using so far, 
it would come back blank. However, all the folders/files still exist in the 
workspace directory, but they don't appear in the WSAD. This problem occurred 
to couple of people on my team. In both cases, it was on Windows 2000.

There was a .log initially created. Based on suggestion from WSAD team, I 
deleted the existing .log file and restarted WSAD. When i restarted WSAD, it 
came back with an empty workspace again, but it did not create a new .log file. 
I have a copy of an old .log file, which may or may not help. I am appending a 
copy of it at the end of this description, since I do not see a way of 
attaching it.

One of the exceptions is from Core so I'm moving this to them for comment. The 
others are from WSAD plugins that are not part of Eclipse.

It looks like there is some corrupt metadata in your workspace. You will need to
give more details. Can you reproduce starting with a new workspace? Is this an
issue where you are upgrading to a newer release using an old workspace? Did the
previous session exit abnormally?

Since the problem happened to two of us, on two different machines, we are both 
providing you with an answer to your comment.  In addition, would the fact that 
this has happened on two unrelated machines tend to reduce the chance of some 
corruption in the environment or user error?


Tijana:
I know I have used only one version of WSAD, which is v5.1.1. I never had a 
different version of WSAD on this machine and never tried to upgrade it. 
However, i remember some message coming up for me regarding some different 
version of WSAD. I ignored it since I've never used nor had a different version 
of WSAD on my machine and it did not make any sense. 
I also do not believe that my session exit abnormally at that time. I also did 
not touch .metadata dir or changed anything else manually.  

Yiying:
In my case, I am not upgrading my WSAD. I installed the new WSAD V5.1.1. I 
consistently can not open the workspace, which used to work for me. I believe 
the .meta data is corrupted. However, I have no idea why this happened, since I 
did not touch .meta data manually.

Without a reproducible Eclipse test case we cannot investigate further. I 
suggest contacting support for the products you are using.
